reviews.text: Good food, nice staff, and a great environment. It's a peaceful place. We ordered different types of foods and baklava. My favorite dish is tave kosi.

Pay attention because they don’t have any menu, they gave us what they wanted, without any additional explanation, and we ended up paying 73 euro in 3 people, like... random prices, totally out of Prishtina average, with the dubt that they apply different treatment to foreigners.

Comparing to quality and prices of a lot of other traditional food restaurants in Prishtina there is no game.

I am sorry but it was a bad overpriced dinner :/

Delicious food at a reasonable price. A more upmarket restaurant for sure, but prices are still very good. The waiter suggested that we try a few dishes, asking us first if we are vegetarians. He bought out 3 half portions with salad and bread. All were delicious!

Have to make reservation, because they offer some food to every table, so they would also prepare them according to the guests amount. Main dishes (the 4 traditionals) meat dish the flavor is amazing!!! To all tastes. Ajvar also very good! best best of all. Wine 28 euro , a bit pricy . Average 22 euro all included. It’s ok. Service also ok, but must with reservation… you can get in and sit…

Best food we had on a three week trip. Served family style in the typical clay pots, so the pictures don't do it justice. But it was so, so delicious.

Thanks for a lovely evening!
